MySQL Commands List with Detailed Description

1. SELECT - Retrieves data from one or more tables. Can specify columns, apply filters, joins, sorting, and aggregation.

2. INSERT - Adds new records into a table. Can insert single or multiple rows using VALUES or from another query.

3. UPDATE - Modifies existing records in a table based on conditions using WHERE clause.

4. DELETE - Removes records from a table. Without WHERE, it deletes all rows.

5. REPLACE - Inserts a new row or replaces an existing row if a duplicate key conflict occurs.

6. CREATE DATABASE - Creates a new database schema to store tables and other objects.

7. DROP DATABASE - Permanently deletes a database and all its contents.

8. ALTER DATABASE - Modifies database properties such as character set or collation.

9. CREATE TABLE - Creates a new table with defined columns, data types, and constraints.

10. DROP TABLE - Deletes a table and all its data permanently.

11. ALTER TABLE - Modifies table structure (add, modify, or drop columns, constraints, indexes).

12. TRUNCATE TABLE - Quickly removes all rows from a table and resets auto-increment values.

13. RENAME TABLE - Changes the name of an existing table.

14. CREATE INDEX - Creates an index on columns to speed up data retrieval operations.

15. DROP INDEX - Removes an index from a table.

16. CREATE VIEW - Creates a virtual table based on a SELECT query; does not store data physically.

17. ALTER VIEW - Modifies the definition of an existing view.

18. DROP VIEW - Deletes a view from the database.

19. CREATE PROCEDURE - Defines a stored procedure (a reusable block of SQL statements).

20. ALTER PROCEDURE - Modifies an existing stored procedure.

21. DROP PROCEDURE - Deletes a stored procedure.

22. CREATE FUNCTION - Defines a user-defined function that returns a value.

23. DROP FUNCTION - Deletes a function.

24. CREATE TRIGGER - Creates a trigger that executes automatically on INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE events.

25. DROP TRIGGER - Removes a trigger.

26. CREATE EVENT - Creates a scheduled task that runs automatically at specified intervals.

27. ALTER EVENT - Modifies a scheduled event.

28. DROP EVENT - Deletes an event.

29. GRANT - Assigns privileges (like SELECT, INSERT) to users or roles.

30. REVOKE - Removes previously granted privileges.

31. START TRANSACTION - Begins a transaction block to execute multiple statements as one unit.

32. BEGIN - Another way to start a transaction (same as START TRANSACTION).

33. COMMIT - Saves all changes made during the transaction permanently.

34. ROLLBACK - Reverts all changes made during the transaction.

35. SAVEPOINT - Creates a checkpoint within a transaction to roll back partially.

36. RELEASE SAVEPOINT - Removes a savepoint.

37. SET TRANSACTION - Defines transaction properties like isolation level.

38. SET AUTOCOMMIT - Enables or disables automatic committing of statements.

39. WHERE - Filters rows based on specified conditions.

40. GROUP BY - Groups rows sharing the same values for aggregation.

41. HAVING - Filters grouped results (used after GROUP BY).

42. ORDER BY - Sorts query results in ascending (ASC) or descending (DESC) order.

43. LIMIT - Restricts the number of rows returned.

44. OFFSET - Skips a specified number of rows before returning results.

45. INNER JOIN - Returns rows that have matching values in both tables.

46. LEFT JOIN - Returns all rows from the left table and matching rows from the right table.

47. RIGHT JOIN - Returns all rows from the right table and matching rows from the left table.

48. CROSS JOIN - Returns all possible combinations of rows (Cartesian product).

49. NATURAL JOIN - Automatically joins tables based on columns with the same names.

50. USING - Specifies common columns for joining tables when column names are identical.

51. AND - Combines multiple conditions; all must be true.

52. OR - Combines conditions; at least one must be true.

53. NOT - Negates a condition.

54. IN - Checks if a value exists within a list of values.

55. BETWEEN - Filters values within a specified inclusive range.

56. LIKE - Searches for patterns using wildcards (% and _).

57. IS NULL - Checks if a column has NULL values.

58. IS NOT NULL - Checks if a column has non-NULL values.

59. EXISTS - Returns true if a subquery returns any rows.

60. ANY - Compares a value with any value returned by a subquery.

61. ALL - Compares a value with all values returned by a subquery.

62. COUNT() - Returns the number of rows or non-null values.

63. SUM() - Calculates total sum of a numeric column.

64. AVG() - Calculates average value of a numeric column.

65. MIN() - Returns smallest value in a column.

66. MAX() - Returns largest value in a column.

67. WITH - Defines a Common Table Expression (temporary result set for a query).

68. WITH RECURSIVE - Defines recursive queries for hierarchical data.

69. ROW_NUMBER() - Assigns unique sequential numbers to rows.

70. RANK() - Assigns rank with gaps for duplicate values.

71. DENSE_RANK() - Assigns rank without gaps.

72. LAG() - Accesses data from previous row.

73. LEAD() - Accesses data from next row.

74. NTILE() - Divides rows into equal groups.

75. USE - Selects a database to work with.

76. SHOW DATABASES - Lists all databases.

77. SHOW TABLES - Lists all tables in current database.

78. SHOW COLUMNS - Displays structure of a table.

79. SHOW INDEX - Displays indexes of a table.

80. SHOW STATUS - Displays server status information.

81. SHOW VARIABLES - Displays system configuration variables.

82. DESCRIBE (DESC) - Shows column details of a table.

83. EXPLAIN - Shows how a query will be executed (execution plan).

84. LOAD DATA INFILE - Imports data from a file into a table.

85. SELECT INTO OUTFILE - Exports query results into a file.

86. LOCK TABLES - Locks tables to control concurrent access.

87. UNLOCK TABLES - Releases locks on tables.

88. DISTINCT - Returns only unique values.

89. AS - Assigns alias names to columns or tables.

90. CASE - Implements conditional logic in queries (like IF-ELSE).

91. UNION - Combines results of multiple queries and removes duplicates.

92. UNION ALL - Combines results including duplicates.